														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-293243">
									

<p>If you're worried about breaking disbelief, how about something like this: <a href="/randomproposal">Random 001 proposal</a></p>
<p>It's not <em>quite</em> random, as there are only a few proposals, and the results are cached for 60 seconds (in other words, it'll only pick a new random proposal per minute, and 'cos there are only a few, it might pick the same one twice in a row).</p>
<p>So, why settle for a single 001, when we can have many? Different one every 60 seconds, and it would maintain the appearance that it's a legit entry.</p>

